 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",100,1

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",100,1

29516049-03d0-479f-bbff-dac944d5a2ce,2026-01-13T17:17:12.460+00:00,2026-01-13T17:17:12.460+00:00,S78027715,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1968077633,QUESTANS97247,11382:QUESTANS:97247,PI1948490065,,KI_18147700,External,Doc1968077637,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All the information requested below is necessary for Qualifying your company as Red Hat Supplier, and for as long as it remains a Red Hat Supplier, your Company must promptly inform Red Hat of any changes to the information you provide in this Supplier Questionnaire.

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",81,1
bfd4d2de-5172-4d17-a5c3-fdd3ebbada7c,2026-01-13T17:17:12.598+00:00,2026-01-13T17:17:12.598+00:00,S78027715,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1968077633,QUESTANS97252,11382:QUESTANS:97252,PI1948490065,,KI_18147701,External,Doc1968077637,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All your company employees in the roles described below are required to complete an integrity training course every 12 months:

 Ethics Training URL : <span style=""color: rgb(0, 3, 255);""><strong>https://training-lms.redhat.com/sso/saml/auth/redhat?RelayState=deeplinkplayerV2%3D80349168</strong></span>

 1) Account manager and/or leader of the Red Hat/Supplier relationship
 2) All employees who are directly involved in negotiating or closing business with government entities with Red Hat or on behalf of Red Hat
 3) All employees who regularly interact with government officials to secure licenses, permits or any government document on behalf of Red Hat
 4) For companies with less than 50 employees, Director of sales (or equivalent function for your organization).

 This Training course should include the following Criteria:

 1) Requires your employees and representatives to comply with all applicable laws
 2) Prohibits your employees and representatives from offering, paying, or promising payments, gifts, or anything of value directly or indirectly to (a) any government officials or employees for the purpose of influencing, obtaining, or retaining any business, or (b) any other person for any unlawful purpose
 3) References Anti-bribery statutes such as the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, U.K. Bribery Act and/or other relevant, local anti-bribery laws

 Many companies have integrity training courses that cover the above elements. If your company does not have an existing training program, Red Hat offers a complimentary web-based integrity training course that can be accessed here Ethics Training.",81,1

da57a9c5-df76-41d1-a4ae-96ec07a1343d,2026-01-29T14:15:27.760+00:00,2026-01-29T14:15:27.760+00:00,S78270009,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1985842579,QUESTANS169001,11382:QUESTANS:169001,PI1948673959,,KI_18172259,External,Doc1985842583,Red Hat Company Ownership - Companies Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All the information requested below is necessary for Qualifying your company as Red Hat Supplier, and for as long as it remains a Red Hat Supplier, your Company must promptly inform Red Hat of any changes to the information you provide in this Supplier Questionnaire.

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",83,2

bad55f21-3d5f-43a3-bfd0-2c20e29b5655,2026-01-29T14:15:34.020+00:00,2026-01-29T14:15:34.020+00:00,S78270009,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1988694336,QUESTANS179014,11382:QUESTANS:179014,PI1948490065,,KI_18147700,External,Doc1988694340,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All the information requested below is necessary for Qualifying your company as Red Hat Supplier, and for as long as it remains a Red Hat Supplier, your Company must promptly inform Red Hat of any changes to the information you provide in this Supplier Questionnaire.

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",83,2
823ff426-6a38-49a7-b3b9-014ea8095542,2026-01-29T14:15:34.153+00:00,2026-01-29T14:15:34.153+00:00,S78270009,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1988694336,QUESTANS179019,11382:QUESTANS:179019,PI1948490065,,KI_18147701,External,Doc1988694340,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All your company employees in the roles described below are required to complete an integrity training course every 12 months:

 Ethics Training URL : <span style=""color: rgb(0, 3, 255);""><strong>https://training-lms.redhat.com/sso/saml/auth/redhat?RelayState=deeplinkplayerV2%3D80349168</strong></span>

 1) Account manager and/or leader of the Red Hat/Supplier relationship
 2) All employees who are directly involved in negotiating or closing business with government entities with Red Hat or on behalf of Red Hat
 3) All employees who regularly interact with government officials to secure licenses, permits or any government document on behalf of Red Hat
 4) For companies with less than 50 employees, Director of sales (or equivalent function for your organization).

 This Training course should include the following Criteria:

 1) Requires your employees and representatives to comply with all applicable laws
 2) Prohibits your employees and representatives from offering, paying, or promising payments, gifts, or anything of value directly or indirectly to (a) any government officials or employees for the purpose of influencing, obtaining, or retaining any business, or (b) any other person for any unlawful purpose
 3) References Anti-bribery statutes such as the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, U.K. Bribery Act and/or other relevant, local anti-bribery laws

 Many companies have integrity training courses that cover the above elements. If your company does not have an existing training program, Red Hat offers a complimentary web-based integrity training course that can be accessed here Ethics Training.",83,2

</div><div><strong>Certification Statements:</strong></div>

</div><div><ol><li>That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.</li><li>You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct</li><li>You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.</li><li>You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.</li><li>Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company.  Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",100,1

<div>Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;
</div><div>In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
</div><div>The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy</div><div>Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy
 
</div><div><strong>Certification Statements:</strong></div> 
<div>By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:
</div><div><ol><li>That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.</li><li>You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct</li><li>You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.</li><li>You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.</li><li>Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. 6d44cb9c-2070-4ba4-a60e-d5916f746237,2026-02-03T10:34:37.664+00:00,2026-02-03T10:34:37.664+00:00,S78361937,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS1990349059,QUESTANS172256,11382:QUESTANS:172256,PI1948673987,,KI_18147704,External,Doc1990349063,Red Hat Ultimate Parent Company Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All the information requested below is necessary for Qualifying your company as Red Hat Supplier, and for as long as it remains a Red Hat Supplier, your Company must promptly inform Red Hat of any changes to the information you provide in this Supplier Questionnaire.

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",100,1

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",84,1
9715fdc9-2092-4f24-a5cb-63d935924192,2026-02-03T14:31:26.096+00:00,2026-02-03T14:31:26.096+00:00,S78426365,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS2004122621,QUESTANS232634,11382:QUESTANS:232634,PI1948490065,,KI_18147701,External,Doc2004122625,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All your company employees in the roles described below are required to complete an integrity training course every 12 months:

 Ethics Training URL : <span style=""color: rgb(0, 3, 255);""><strong>https://training-lms.redhat.com/sso/saml/auth/redhat?RelayState=deeplinkplayerV2%3D80349168</strong></span>

 1) Account manager and/or leader of the Red Hat/Supplier relationship
 2) All employees who are directly involved in negotiating or closing business with government entities with Red Hat or on behalf of Red Hat
 3) All employees who regularly interact with government officials to secure licenses, permits or any government document on behalf of Red Hat
 4) For companies with less than 50 employees, Director of sales (or equivalent function for your organization).

 This Training course should include the following Criteria:

 1) Requires your employees and representatives to comply with all applicable laws
 2) Prohibits your employees and representatives from offering, paying, or promising payments, gifts, or anything of value directly or indirectly to (a) any government officials or employees for the purpose of influencing, obtaining, or retaining any business, or (b) any other person for any unlawful purpose
 3) References Anti-bribery statutes such as the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, U.K. Bribery Act and/or other relevant, local anti-bribery laws

 Many companies have integrity training courses that cover the above elements. If your company does not have an existing training program, Red Hat offers a complimentary web-based integrity training course that can be accessed here Ethics Training.",84,1

</div><div><strong>Certification Statements:</strong></div> 
<div>By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. 7838cb01-889a-4a23-8418-20aaf9f903a5,2026-02-03T14:38:05.677+00:00,2026-02-03T14:38:05.677+00:00,S78417166,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS2001792841,QUESTANS221534,11382:QUESTANS:221534,PI1948490065,,KI_18147700,External,Doc2001792845,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All the information requested below is necessary for Qualifying your company as Red Hat Supplier, and for as long as it remains a Red Hat Supplier, your Company must promptly inform Red Hat of any changes to the information you provide in this Supplier Questionnaire.

 Privacy Policy
 To Supplier Company:
 PRIVACY NOTICE:

 Red Hat will process, store, and in general manage personal information contained in this Questionnaire for purposes of assessing your Company and its personnel and resources in connection with our relationship with your Company;

 In order to comply with the US Foreign Corrupt Practices, Act and other applicable anti-corruption laws, Red Hat may use suppliers to conduct the adverse media checks and other reviews to determine if your Company or its personnel and other resources have not violated any laws or regulations.
 The Bureau van Dijk (a Moody's Analytics company) privacy statement is available here : https://www.bvdinfo.com/en-gb/product-privacy-policy

 Red Hat's general privacy practices that apply to personal information Red Hat collects, uses and shares are described in Red Hat’s Privacy Statement at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/privacy-policy

 Certification Statements:
 By completing and submitting this Supplier Questionnaire, you and your Company further certify:

 1. That all information and answers you have furnished in this Supplier Questionnaire are truthful, accurate, and complete, and your Company will report to Red Hat promptly any changes in the information provided.
 2. You acknowledge that have read and agree to the terms of the Red Hat Supplier Code of Conduct available at: https://www.redhat.com/en/about/policies/procurement/supplier-code-of-conduct
 3. You certify that your Company will complete an integrity training and integrity questionnaires when requested.
 4. You guarantee that you have provided the required notices identified above to all persons referenced herein.
 5. Your company is responsible for safeguarding the Ariba Account Credentials, and that only authorized personnel are allowed to use them. Definitions: As used in this Supplier Questionnaire, the term: “Board Members” includes all of the members of a company’s Board of Directors or any equivalent or comparable governing body or group. “Company” includes any company, corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other entity. It also includes Organizations as Universities, Landlords as well as Freelancers. “Government” includes any (a) national, state or local government, (b) public international organization (such as the United Nations), (c) agency or company subject to a country's public procurement laws and (d) company that is owned or controlled by a government, organization, agency or company described in items (a), (b), (c) or (d) of this definition (such as a state-owned oil or telephone company). “Senior Management” includes (a) all of a company’s officers, presidents, senior vice presidents, managing directors, directors of sales, finance and marketing and all members of a company’s senior leadership teams, (b) if a company does not have “officers”, “presidents”, “senior vice presidents”, “managing directors”, or “directors of sales, finance or marketing”, then those persons holding equivalent or comparable positions to those and (c) those persons (other than administrative personnel, such as secretarial assistants) who report to the positions / persons covered by items (a) and (b). ”Ultimate Parent” is the top-level company in a family of companies. An Ultimate Parent directly or indirectly controls a company. In the following example, Company D is Company A’s Ultimate Parent: - Company A is controlled by Company B; - Company B is controlled by Company C; - Company C is controlled by Company D; and - No company controls Company D. “English Language” – is using the basic Latin Alphabet character set (A-Z) “Local Language” and “Na",82,1
02402b25-88c8-4333-ab42-42028d5d3666,2026-02-03T14:38:05.818+00:00,2026-02-03T14:38:05.818+00:00,S78417166,QUESTIONNAIRE,WS2001792841,QUESTANS221539,11382:QUESTANS:221539,PI1948490065,,KI_18147701,External,Doc2001792845,Red Hat Integrity Training Questionnaire,String,Requirement,"All your company employees in the roles described below are required to complete an integrity training course every 12 months:

 Ethics Training URL : <span style=""color: rgb(0, 3, 255);""><strong>https://training-lms.redhat.com/sso/saml/auth/redhat?RelayState=deeplinkplayerV2%3D80349168</strong></span>

 1) Account manager and/or leader of the Red Hat/Supplier relationship
 2) All employees who are directly involved in negotiating or closing business with government entities with Red Hat or on behalf of Red Hat
 3) All employees who regularly interact with government officials to secure licenses, permits or any government document on behalf of Red Hat
 4) For companies with less than 50 employees, Director of sales (or equivalent function for your organization).

 This Training course should include the following Criteria:

 1) Requires your employees and representatives to comply with all applicable laws
 2) Prohibits your employees and representatives from offering, paying, or promising payments, gifts, or anything of value directly or indirectly to (a) any government officials or employees for the purpose of influencing, obtaining, or retaining any business, or (b) any other person for any unlawful purpose
 3) References Anti-bribery statutes such as the U.S. Foreign Corrupt Practices Act, U.K. Bribery Act and/or other relevant, local anti-bribery laws

 Many companies have integrity training courses that cover the above elements. If your company does not have an existing training program, Red Hat offers a complimentary web-based integrity training course that can be accessed here Ethics Training.",82,1
